Chobits series? So Chi is...

270
00:17:02,433 --> 00:17:03,433
What's Chi?

271
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,000
Chi is Chi.

272
00:17:05,066 --> 00:17:07,433
Chi is the name
Hideki gave to Chi.

273
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:09,233
Yeah, but why "Chi"?

274
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:10,133
In the beginning,

275
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:13,266
the only thing Chi
could say was "chi."

276
00:17:17,466 --> 00:17:18,466
That sounds like
the kind of name

277
00:17:18,533 --> 00:17:21,066
you'd give to a dog or a cat.

278
00:17:23,866 --> 00:17:25,400
Anyway, I'll analyze you

279
00:17:25,466 --> 00:17:27,166
and tell you
what you really are.

280
00:17:31,566 --> 00:17:32,233
If you need anything,

281
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:33,800
feel free to tell Kotoko,

282
00:17:33,866 --> 00:17:35,533
and I'm sure she
can take care of it.

283
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,633
Okay, I'll see you later.

284
00:17:42,566 --> 00:17:43,300
But...

285
00:17:43,366 --> 00:17:45,233
Hm?

286
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:48,600
"Chi" is the name
that Hideki gave Chi.

287
00:17:48,666 --> 00:17:51,900
Hideki gave this name to Chi...

288
00:17:51,966 --> 00:17:56,433
Hideki gave, that's
why Chi loves this name.

289
00:18:05,566 --> 00:18:06,566
Oh?

290
00:18:42,666 --> 00:18:44,566
I'm sorry, Chi.

291
00:18:45,066 --> 00:18:48,966
I made a promise that
I wouldn't do anything.

292
00:18:49,033 --> 00:18:51,200
A promise I made to him.

293
00:19:00,266 --> 00:19:01,700
I never expected that something

294
00:19:01,766 --> 00:19:03,200
like this would come up.

295
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:17,166
Well, I failed again.

296
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:18,900
No matter how many times I trace

297
00:19:18,966 --> 00:19:22,600
the sender of this image,
it's always a dead end.

298
00:19:22,666 --> 00:19:25,766
Whoever it is, they've
done an awfully good job.

299
00:19:26,533 --> 00:19:27,500
I'm sorry.

300
00:19:27,566 --> 00:19:28,400
Huh?

301
00:19:28,466 --> 00:19:29,500
I don't believe it's possible

302
00:19:29,566 --> 00:19:31,966
for my present
configuration to handle this,

303
00:19:32,033 --> 00:19:33,733
so I'll stop.

304
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:35,600
It's not your fault, Yuzuki.

305
00:19:35,666 --> 00:19:38,000
I'm afraid I'm just not
experienced enough.

306
00:19:38,066 --> 00:19:40,500
But then, I was made
to be helpful to you,

307
00:19:40,566 --> 00:19:43,033
and if I can't do what
you ask me, I'm not.

308
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:46,233
To think that I can't
do what I'm asked to do.

309
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:50,500
Huh? Lord Minoru?

310
00:19:50,566 --> 00:19:53,433
You are very helpful
to me, Yuzuki.

311
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:54,500
So much so in fact,

312
00:19:54,566 --> 00:19:56,833
that sometimes it
actually troubles me.

313
00:19:59,733 --> 00:20:01,666
When you were much
younger, Lord Minoru,

314
00:20:01,733 --> 00:20:03,633
if anything ever made
you sad for a while,

315
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:05,000
your sister was
always right here,

316
00:20:05,066 --> 00:20:06,733
to do something like this.

317
00:20:07,066 --> 00:20:08,100
Yuzuki.

318
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:08,966
It's been a while

319
00:20:09,033 --> 00:20:10,533
since the last
maintenance was done,

320
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,133
but there still hasn't
been any new data entered

321
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,433
regarding your elder sister.

322
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:16,366
In order for me
to be closer to her

323
00:20:16,433 --> 00:20:18,100
and serve you better,
Lord Minoru,

324
00:20:18,166 --> 00:20:21,966
please enter more
data about your sister.

325
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:25,433
You know I-

326
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:26,966
Lord Minoru?

327
00:20:30,666 --> 00:20:32,266
A telephone call.

328
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:32,966
Who is it?

329
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,566
It's Mr. Motosuwa.

330
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:37,133
At this time of night?

331
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:38,333
Connect me.

332
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:40,233
Connecting.

333
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:42,833
Minoru! I can't
find Chi; she's gone!

334
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:45,700
She disappeared;
I don't know what happened!

335
00:20:45,766 --> 00:20:47,033
That sounds serious.

336
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:48,533
Do you have any leads?

337
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,466
There was a guy at the bookstore
who found her hairclip,

338
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:54,033
but somehow she just
suddenly disappeared!

339
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:55,166
I looked all over for her,

340
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:57,100
and I can't find
any sign of her.

341
00:20:57,366 --> 00:20:58,066
Shinbo's not around,

342
00:20:58,133 --> 00:20:59,433
so I don't know what to do.

343
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,566
You're the only one
I can turn to, Minoru!

344
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:03,466
Okay, try to calm
down, Motosuwa!

345
00:21:03,533 --> 00:21:04,466
I don't know.

346
00:21:04,533 --> 00:21:05,966
I've just got a really
bad feeling about this!

347
00:21:06,033 --> 00:21:06,833
Yeah, I understand.

348
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:08,333
Just meet me at the Duklyon.

349
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,600
I'll be right over.

350
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:13,300
The connection has
been terminated.

351
00:21:13,366 --> 00:21:14,633
I'm going out now.

352
00:21:16,166 --> 00:21:17,633
There's a chance I might
need to look something up

353
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:19,566
when I'm out with
Motosuwa later on.

354
00:21:19,633 --> 00:21:21,033
Would you like to come with me?

355
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:22,700
Sure.

356
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:24,833
Yuzuki, you always seem

357
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,733
to have the same exact
smile on your face

358
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:29,033
whenever we're going to
do something together.

359
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:32,133
It's because I know I'll be
by your side, Lord Minoru.

360
00:21:39,966 --> 00:21:40,833
Well, shall we go?

361
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:41,966
Yes.

362
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:48,600
Chi.

363
00:21:50,033 --> 00:21:51,066
But after a while,

364
00:21:51,133 --> 00:21:53,733
her husband only seemed
interested in the Persocom.

365
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:56,433
Do you find
Persocoms attractive?

366
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:57,400
Is it more fun to be

367
00:21:57,466 --> 00:21:59,700
with a Persocom
than with a human?

368
00:22:01,433 --> 00:22:04,933
No one'll want to stay by
anyone's side anymore.

369
00:22:06,233 --> 00:22:07,633
That's beside the point;

370
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:09,666
I still have to look for Chi.

371
00:22:09,733 --> 00:22:10,733
Let's go, Sumomo!

372
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:11,866
Aye!

373
00:22:11,933 --> 00:22:13,366
Chi, please be alright!

374
00:23:58,766 --> 00:23:59,533
Okay.

375
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:01,666
Let's say my wallet disappears.

376
00:24:01,733 --> 00:24:03,566
The missing wallet's
not gonna be worried

377
00:24:03,633 --> 00:24:05,833
or lonely or anything like that.

378
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:07,600
And, of course, contents aside,

379
00:24:07,666 --> 00:24:10,366
I'm not gonna be worried
about the wallet either.

380
00:24:11,633 --> 00:24:13,466
Chi is a Persocom.

381
00:24:13,533 --> 00:24:16,366
She might not feel
doubt or loneliness.

382
00:24:16,433 --> 00:24:19,700
But not me; I'm super
worried about her!

